The paper discusses a new way to quantify and compute the information of objects, which is a problem of interest in several subfields of computer science. The use of hierarchical coding and algorithmic complexity suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The focus on computation and complexity also suggests connections to computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of representation and classification could also relate to machine learning (cs.LG).
